  "texts": [
    "In selfplay settings, the participating agents are of the same type.",
    "In Cross-Play experiments, we pair agents with unseen partners, and they need to adapt their behavior to the actions of these new partners.",
    "AgentsTo allow LLMs to play multi-turn games, we scaffold them with an agentic framework based on Cognitive Architectures for Language Agents Sumers et al. (2023).",
    "The framework includes three parts: Memory, Reasoning, and Grounding.Memory includes (1) Long-Term Memory for storing the Game Description, including the game's rules, conventions, objectives, and action space, (2) Working memory, which consists of a textual description of the current observation, and (3) Episodic Memory which is a list of previous actions selected by the agent.Reasoning is where the Large Language Model (LLM) is plugged into the framework.",
    "It takes the textual description from the Memory as input and generates the next action based on the context."
  ],
